result.name: 達人包車 Dalin Pocha

reviews.text: Great fried chicken, very crispy and tender. And decent menu of other dishes. Service was good but could be improved—had a difficult time trying to order even in Cantonese and had to supplement with some Mandarin. Would caution if you do not speak either when dining here. But otherwise very accommodating and my baby cousins loved it here.

Good, friendly customer service. Open late which was great as we got in at about 1 AM.

We tried the beef noodle soup which was hot, but tasted like water and the beef had just been boiled unseasoned. It wasn't good at all. 

However, we also tried the honey fried chicken , and the fried chicken as well as the french fries were great. If this was just a Korean fried chicken place, it would be five stars. 

The kimchi and pickles were good, as was the salad that came with the chicken. They had a great selection of soju and drinks as well.

dishes are well cooked in big portion. 
suggest coming in a group of 4~6 to enjoy a frrat variety of korean dishes.
fried chicken is goodddd.
reservation is recommended.

This place used to be very good , the chicken were great and the KR food was so good. But I think the standard had drop and the price are quite expensive. when compare to the whole street. there are many other options. I think I will give it a miss for a while. For two person for two dish it was 7XXHKD.  Also the air con doesnt seem to be working, they need to use a Fan

Korean restaurant with Korean staff, comfortable seating arrangement but table was too small for 4 people with the food we ordered. They have some interesting things in the menu for example the ‘bag of blood’ which is actually pomegranate with alcohol. Was easy to make last minute booking on Saturday (called at 6pm for 8.30pm) with no issues. Food was ok, not fantastic.

reviews.text: 2016年曾經同朋友喺到食過一次飯，當晚覺得食物質素唔錯，事隔三年故地重遊，發現無以前咁好食，雖然紫菜包飯同埋炸雞都唔差 但係排骨令人失望，醬汁只有鹹味，芝士無芝士味，年糕煮半日個芯都仲係硬嘅。

Good, friendly customer service. Open late which was great as we got in at about 1 AM.

We tried the beef noodle soup which was hot, but tasted like water and the beef had just been boiled unseasoned. It wasn't good at all. 

However, we also tried the honey fried chicken , and the fried chicken as well as the french fries were great. If this was just a Korean fried chicken place, it would be five stars. 

The kimchi and pickles were good, as was the salad that came with the chicken. They had a great selection of soju and drinks as well.
